.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCH-ACCOUNTNO 1 "July 16, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-match-accountno \- Match received payments by bank account number in AbraFlexi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-match-accountno
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-match-accountno
is a script that matches received payments in AbraFlexi based on the sender's bank account number. It searches for payments by account number (directly, or via the company that account is registered to) and attempts to match them to corresponding issued invoices.
.SH OPTIONS
This script uses environment variables for configuration. Common options include:
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Path to the output JSON report file (default: match_accountno_report.json)
.TP
.B MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
Number of days to look back for payments (default: 365)
.TP
.B MATCHER_LOCALIZE
Locale for log/report messages: en_US (default), cs_CZ, or sk_SK.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PARTIAL_MATCH
Settle underpaid invoices (partial payments) automatically instead of leaving them for manual review (default: false)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The script requires AbraFlexi connection details:
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.SH MATCHING LOGIC
Domestic payments are matched by account number together with bank code
(buc + smerKod); the account number alone is not unique across banks, so a
payment whose bank code differs from the invoice's recorded one is not
matched, even if the account number is identical. Foreign payments, which
carry no account number/bank code, are matched by IBAN instead (IBAN
whitespace formatting differences between bank imports and manually
entered invoices are normalized before comparing). An account number or
IBAN found registered to more than one company in AbraFlexi's address
book is reported under
.I duplicate_buc
in the JSON report instead of being guessed at, together with the
conflicting companies and the payment document(s) affected.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I match_accountno_report.json
Default output file containing the matching results in JSON format
compliant with the multiflexi report schema, including the
.I matched ,
.I unmatched ,
.I multiple ,
.I overpaid ,
.I underpaid
and
.I duplicate_buc
metrics.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-matcher (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-out (1),
